urn_count': 17, 'current_player_index': 1,", "'player1_node': 1, 'player2_node': 3}", "and return a dictionary that contains the following keys:", "'game_state': a copy of the input game_state dictionary", "'adjudicator': a string, one of 'simulated_annealing', 'quantum_annealing', 'schrodinger_equation'", "'winner': if both players have chosen vertices, a string, one of 'red', 'blue', 'draw', otherwise None", "'score': if both players have chosen vertices, the difference in influence scores as a real number, otherwise None", "'influence_vector': a vector of real numbers of length vertex_count (one real number per vertex in the game graph)", "'correlation_matrix': symmetric real-valued matrix of spin-spin correlations with zeros on diagonals", "'parameters': a copy of the parameters dictionary"]}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.adjudicators.adjudicate.Adjudicator.schrodinger_equation", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "game_state", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.adjudicators.adjudicate.Adjudicator.quantum_annealing", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "game_state", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.adjudicators.adjudicate.Adjudicator.lookup_table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "game_state", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.generate_terminal_states", "documentation": ["generates unique terminal states, states related to them by symmetry, and game_state objects for them "], "functions": [{"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.generate_terminal_states.convert_state_string_to_game_state", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "graph", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "terminal_state_string", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.generate_terminal_states.generate_all_tangled_terminal_states", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "graph_number", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.generate_terminal_states.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.schrodinger", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.how_to_adjudicate_states", "documentation": ["how to use provided solvers to adjudicate Tangled terminal states "], "functions": [{"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.how_to_adjudicate_states.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.find_hardware_embeddings", "documentation": ["given a D-Wave processor (target graph) and a source graph, find as many embeddings as possible of the source\ngraph into the target hardware graph "], "functions": [{"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.find_hardware_embeddings.get_zephyr_subgrid", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "qubit_connectivity_graph", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rows", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cols", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "gridsize", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Make a subgraph of a Zephyr (Advantage2) graph on a set of rows and columns of unit cells.\n\nArgs:\n    qubit_connectivity_graph (nx.Graph): Qubit connectivity graph\n    rows (Iterable): Iterable of rows of unit cells to include\n    cols (Iterable): Iterable of columns of unit cells to include\n    gridsize: Int\n\nReturns:\n    nx.Graph: The subgraph of qubit_connectivity_graph induced on the nodes in \"rows\" and \"cols\""]}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.find_hardware_embeddings.get_independent_embeddings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "embs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Finds a list of non-overlapping embeddings in `embs`.\n\nArgs:\n    embs (list[dict]): a list of embeddings (dict)\n\nReturns:\n    List[dict]: a list of embeddings (dict)"]}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.find_hardware_embeddings.search_for_subgraphs_in_subgrid", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "subgrid_graph", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "subgraph", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_embeddings", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Find a list of subgraph (embeddings) in a subgrid.\n\nArgs:\n    subgrid_graph (nx.Graph): a subgrid\n    subgraph (nx.Graph): subgraphs in subgrid_graph to search for\n    timeout (int, optional): time limit for search. Defaults to 20.\n    max_embeddings (int, optional): maximum number of embeddings to look for. Defaults to np.inf.\n    verbose (bool, optional): Flag for verbosity. Defaults to True.\n\nReturns:\n    List[dict]: a list of embeddings"]}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.find_hardware_embeddings.raster_embedding_search", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "hardware_graph", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "subgraph", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "raster_breadth", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "delete_used", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "gridsize", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a matrix (n, L) of subgraph embeddings to hardware_graph.\n\nArgs:\n    hardware_graph (nx.Graph): target graph to embed to\n    subgraph (nx.Graph): A smaller graph to embed into hardware_graph\n    raster_breadth (int, optional): Breadth parameter of raster search. Defaults to 5.\n    delete_used (bool, optional): Flag whether nodes in hardware_graph can appear in multiple embeddings.\n                                  If set to true, nodes cannot be used in multiple embeddings. Defaults to True.\n    verbose (bool, optional): Whether to print progress. Defaults to True.\n    gridsize (int, optional): Size of grid. Defaults to 16.\n\nReturns:\n    numpy.ndarray: a matrix of embeddings"]}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.find_hardware_embeddings.get_embeddings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "source_graph_number", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "qc_solver_to_use", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.game_graph_properties", "documentation": ["stores properties of game graphs "], "functions": [{"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.game_graph_properties.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.game_graph_properties.GraphProperties", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "tangled_adjudicate.utils.game_graph_properties.GraphProperties.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "graph_number", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A Tangled game graph is specified by a graph number, which label specific graphs included here. In this module there", "are 10 included graphs numbered 1 through 10. Each graph requires specification of vertex count (